# `lic` repo boundary (compiler only)

**`lic` = the Li compiler, std library, language/verification docs, and harnesses that prove the toolchain.**  
Do **not** use `lic` as the home for World Studio product work, UX galleries, or deployable app demos.

## Belongs in `lic`

| Area | Examples |
|------|----------|
| Compiler | `compiler/`, bootstrap, codegen, `lic build` / `lic check` |
| Standard library | `std/**` |
| Language & proof | `docs/language/`, `docs/verification/`, `docs/semantics/` |
| Toolchain tests | `li-tests/` (compiler + composable gates **as harness**) |
| Tier benchmarks | `benchmarks/` on **lic** (physics/numerics kernels under test) |
| Build/CI for **lic** | `scripts/build.sh`, agent-kit sync, repo CI |

## Do **not** add to `lic`

| Off-limits | Put it here instead |
|------------|---------------------|
| HTML/JS studio showcase (no PNG/WebM in git) | **`studio-app`** → `demo/` · capture: `scripts/capture-studio-mockup-screenshots.sh` → `.artifacts/` |
| `deploy/studio-demo/`, new `deploy/*` product sites | **`studio-app`** — see `deploy/studio-demo/MOVED.md` |
| Product UX canon, planned UI galleries | **`studio-app/docs/`** — not **`studio`** (that's `import studio`) |
| Competitive-intel media blobs | Gitignored paths only; analysis may stay in docs if harness-relevant |
| New marketing / preview / `preview.html` pages | **`studio-app`** |
| App shell, native binary | **`studio-app`** + **`gui`** |

**Package mirrors** (`packages/studio`, …) may remain in the monorepo **only** for composable `lic check` integration — do **not** grow new product UI, demos, or deploy trees under `lic/`.

## Agent checklist (before committing)

1. Is this change required for **compiler, std, proof, or lic harness**? If no → **other repo**.
2. Am I adding files under `deploy/` (except existing MMO/spin-up until migrated)? → **stop**.
3. Am I adding images/video/HTML for humans to preview Studio? → **`studio-app/demo/`**.

**Imports:** `docs/ecosystem/package-import-naming.md` · **App:** `docs/ecosystem/studio-naming.md`
